Place the tempeh in a shallow flat-bottomed dish. In a small bowl, combine the shoyu, vinegar, sesame oil, and water. Pour over the tempeh and let marinate for 1 hour. Place the marinated tempeh on a heated grill over medium heat. Cook 5 to 6 minutes on each side or until browned. Cut into Â¼-inch cubes and set aside. Bring a large pot of water and the salt to boil. Add the mustard greens and cook uncovered for 3 minutes, or until they are blanched and wilted. Drain the greens and transfer to a serving bowl. Add the tempeh cubes and toss together, Serve immediately.